She left her job as a journalist at The Guardian to pursue writing full-time after the success of her first novel, Homecoming. In 2014 her first thriller, Missing, Presumed introduced Manon Bradshaw, and sold 250,000 copies.  As a child Steiner was diagnosed with retinitis pigmentosa, causing tunnel vision. She was declared blind when she was 41. She died of a brain tumour, diagnosed in 2019. She is survived by her husband Tom Happold and their two sons.  Susie Steiner, born June 27, 1971 â€“ died July 2, 2022, aged 51